    address:'C. de la Cruz 39, Centro, 28012 Madrid',mapCoords:'40.4147474,-3.7028291',
    longDesc:'Matador leans into Madrid tradition with theatricality and warmth. The anchovies in vinegar are sharp and clean, the Iberian ham is carved at the counter, and the Tortilla Española is the thick, barely-set Castilian style that locals argue about for decades. Flamenco-style tapas arrive with the drama the name demands.',
